        public play.mvc.Result remove(play.mvc.Http.Request request)
                       throws ForbiddenException,
                              BadRequestException,
                              NotFoundException
        POST request that removes all StudyResults specified in the parameter. The parameter is a comma separated list of StudyResults IDs as a String. Removing a StudyResult always removes it's ComponentResults.

        public play.mvc.Result tableDataByBatch(java.lang.Long batchId,
                                        java.lang.String workerType)
                                 throws ForbiddenException,
                                        NotFoundException,
                                        BadRequestException
        GET that returns all StudyResults of a Batch in JSON format. As an additional parameter the worker type can be specified and the results will only be of this type. It streams in chunks (reduces memory usage)
